 <div id="body" class="container main">
            <br/><br/><br/>
	    <h1>Help</h1>
            <p>The following description will help determine what you may want to specify for the message and command options when communicating with the trafficlight or the message marquee.</p>
            <p>The command parameters sent to the traffic light are a series of individual commands that represent either a command to turn a light on or off, or a command to delay for a small period of time between changing lights.
            <ul>
              <li>R - turn the RED light ON</li>
              <li>r - turn the RED light OFF</li>
              <li>Y - turn the YELLOW light ON</li>
              <li>y - turn the YELLOW light OFF</li>
              <li>G - turn the GREEN light ON</li>
              <li>g - turn the GREEN light OFF</li>
              <li>- (hyphen) - will add a half second delay to to the sequence</li>
              <li>. (period) - will add a quarter of a second delay to to the sequence</li>
              <li>, (comma)  - will add a tenth of a second delay to to the sequence</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The text modes also need a little clarification.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>rotate - runs acrossed the screen from the right</li>
              <li>hold - appears in the middle of the screen</li>
              <li>flash - words flash on the screen</li>
              <li>scroll - words scroll up from the bottom</li>
              <li>auto - a crazy combination fo display types (some not listed here)</li>
              <li>compressed - compressed letters streaming across the display from right to left</li>
            </ul>
</div>

